e-title','Will saving poor children lead to overpopulation?'),(588,'a-VideoFile-about','Here we show that this misconception isn\'t just wrong, it\'s actually quite the opposite.'),(589,'video-51-subtitles','A common misunderstanding is that if we save all the poor children: the world will become overpopulated.'),(590,'video-51-subtitles','This may sound logical, but it\'s wrong.'),(591,'video-51-subtitles','Its the other way around!'),(592,'video-51-subtitles','Saving the poor childrens lives is required to end population growth.'),(593,'video-51-subtitles','Now! Look at the UN numbers.'),(594,'video-51-subtitles','Poor parents on avarage have five children. And one dies.'),(595,'video-51-subtitles','Look! Two parents are replaced by four surviving children in the next generation.'),(596,'video-51-subtitles','This means the population is growing very fast among the poorest.'),(597,'video-51-subtitles','This is the avarage family in the worst of places like Congo and Afghanistan.'),(598,'video-51-subtitles','Today, where child mortality is highest, that\'s where the population is growing faster than anywhere else.'),(599,'video-51-subtitles','How many people live like this?'),(600,'video-51-subtitles','There are seven billion people in the world. One block: one billion.'),(601,'video-51-subtitles','The poorest two billion...'),(602,'video-51-subtitles','...they live like this.'),(603,'video-51-subtitles','The other five billion...'),(604,'video-51-subtitles','...they have this avarage family. Two parents having two children and there are few child deaths.'),(605,'video-51-subtitles','This is the majority of the world population, not only Europe and the US.'),(606,'video-51-subtitles','It\'s throughout religions and cultures: China, Iran, Mexico, large cities in Africa.'),(607,'video-51-subtitles','Today in most populations children just replace parents.'),(608,'video-51-subtitles','And the size of generations are no longer increasing.'),(609,'video-51-subtitles','This means: the population will stop growing.'),(610,'video-51-subtitles','How did so many people end up with small families?'),(611,'video-51-subtitles','Well,  their children stopped dying.'),(612,'video-51-subtitles','As they left extreme poverty and girls got education: parents no longer had to'),(613,'video-51-subtitles','compensate for child death by having many babies. And a large family stopped being'),(614,'video-51-subtitles','an economic necessity or a social status symbol.'),(615,'video-51-subtitles','And with modern contraceptives: parents across the world, the majority'),(616,'video-51-subtitles','decided to have a small family.'),(617,'video-51-subtitles','So by saving the lives of poor children and helping the last two billion out of poverty:'),(618,'video-51-subtitles','These parents will also decide to have fewer children.'),(619,'video-51-subtitles','And fewer.'),(620,'video-51-subtitles','Eventually...'),(621,'video-51-subtitles','...reaching the two child family'),(622,'video-51-subtitles','That showed the UN family size forcast up to the end of the century.'),(623,'video-51-subtitles','Then the world population is expected to stop growing.'),(624,'video-51-subtitles','Before it stops: another four billion people will be added to the world population.'),(625,'video-51-subtitles','Four billion more. That\'s a lot of people!'),(626,'video-51-subtitles','But the longer poor children keeps dying and this change is delayed:'),(627,'video-51-subtitles','the more billions will be added.'),(628,'video-51-subtitles','So ending population growth starts by saving the poorest children.'),(629,'video-1-subtitles','[HANS ROSLING - Professor International Health Karolinska Institute Sweden]f'),(630,'video-42-subtitles','This shows babies born per woman in the world as a whole.'),(631,'video-42-subtitles','And back in history, all the way up to the year 1800'),(632,'video-42-subtitles','on avarage, there was about 6 babies born per woman.'),(633,'video-42-subtitl