INSERT INTO `video_file` VALUES (1,1,NULL,'as dfasdf',NULL,'asdfasd fasdf','asd fasdfas',47,49,NULL,49,'1\r\n00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,500\r\n[POPULATION OF REGIONS]\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:06,000\r\n[HANS ROSLING - Professor International Health Karolinska Institute Sweden]f\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:00:06,601 --> 00:00:09,500\r\nNow I will show where in the World people live.\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:13,500\r\nThis World Map is divided into four regions of almost the same size.\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:16,800\r\nAmerica, Europe, Africa, Asia.\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:20,500\r\nToday we are seven Billion people in the World.\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:00:20,501 --> 00:00:21,750\r\nWhere do they live?\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:00:21,751 --> 00:00:24,500\r\nOne Billion live in America.\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:00:24,501 --> 00:00:26,900\r\nOne in Europe.\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:29,000\r\nOne in Africa.\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:00:29,001 --> 00:00:32,500\r\nAnd four Billion in Asia.\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,899\r\nEasy to remember:\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:00:34,901 --> 00:00:36,800\r\nOne, one, one, four.\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:00:36,801 --> 00:00:41,000\r\nIn the future there will be more people. Where and how many?\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:46,750\r\nThis line shows the size of the world population\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:51,500\r\nfrom the year 1800. From one Billion to 7 Billion today.\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,750\r\nWhen I went to school back here\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:56,750\r\nthere were three Billion in the World.\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:00:57,399 --> 00:01:02,100\r\nAt that time the United Nations Population experts made a prediction.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,900\r\nIt looked almost exactly like this.\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:05,899\r\nThey were correct.\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,299\r\nAnd now they have made a new prediction. It looks like this:\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:01:10,599 --> 00:01:12,899\r\nThey say the growth will continue:\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:17,299\r\neight, nine and then the fast population growth will end.\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:21,500\r\nWe will be around 10 Billion people in the year 2100.\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:01:21,501 --> 00:01:23,800\r\nSo, three Billion more.\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:27,100\r\nWhere will they live?\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,250\r\nNo more Billion in America.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:01:29,251 --> 00:01:31,500\r\nNo more in Europe.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:33,000\r\nOne more in Asia.\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:39,000\r\nAnd most probably, two Billion more in Africa.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:44,500\r\nBy the time the population growth is over,\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:01:44,501 --> 00:01:49,000\r\nthere will be one, one, three, five Billion.\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:01:49,799 --> 00:01:53,500\r\nSo the experts say that the African population will triple,\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:01:53,501 --> 00:01:56,000\r\nfrom one Billion to three Billion.\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:01:56,001 --> 00:02:00,000\r\nWhen people hear that, the most common reaction is: \"That´s impossible!\"\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:06,099\r\nWhen I went to school, the Asian population was bit more than one Billion.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:02:06,299 --> 00:02:11,300\r\nAnd the experts said, within 50 years, the Asian population will triple.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:14,399\r\nAnd the common reaction was: \"That´s impossible!\"\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:18,500\r\nThis is the number of people today.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:02:18,501 --> 00:02:21,500\r\nLook at Asia: the experts were right.\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:27,250\r\nAnd most likely, the same thing will happen in Africa,\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,750\r\nbefore population growth stops.\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:34,250\r\nSo, this is South America. North America.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:02:35,099 --> 00:02:37,900\r\nWest Europe. East Europe.\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:02:37,901 --> 00:02:40,500\r\nThe people of North America and West Europe\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:02:40,501 --> 00:02:42,900\r\nhave dominated World Economy for a long time.\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:46,750\r\nIn the future they will only be 10 percent of World population.\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,400\r\nBy the end of population growth,\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:02:49,401 --> 00:02:52,841\r\n80 percent will be living in Asia and Africa.\r\n\r\n',48,'2013-06-17 13:57:41','2014-01-28 09:34:01',NULL,15,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'as-dfasf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2013-09-14 23:16:56','2013-11-17 18:27:01',NULL,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2013-10-07 15:43:33','2013-11-27 21:54:14',NULL,65,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,14,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NU